250 g Ground Turkey
6 unit(s) Flour Tortillas
¾ cup Mozzarella Cheese, shredded
1 tbsp Garlic Puree
½ cup Marinara Sauce
¼ cup Roasted Pepper Pesto
100 g Ricotta Cheese
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper
1.5 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Core, then cut pepper into 1/2-inch slices.
Stir together ricotta and half the pesto in a small bowl.

Heat a large non-stick pan over high heat.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then sausage, garlic puree and peppers.
Cook, breaking up turkey into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.**
Season with salt and pepper.

On a clean surface, arrange tortillas.
Add turkey mixture down the middle of each tortilla, the dollop ricotta-pesto mixture over top.
Sprinkle with mozzarella.
Roll tortillas tightly over filling, then arrange wraps on a foil-lined baking sheet, seam-sides down.

Brush wraps with 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil.
Broil in the middle of the oven, until golden-brown, 3-4 min.

Stir together marinara and remaining roasted pepper pesto in a microwaveable bowl.
Cover and microwave on high until warmed through, 1-2 min.
Divide wraps between plates. Serve pesto marinara on the side for dipping.

If you've opted to get turkey, cook it in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the Italian sausage.**